      "content": "but you said they're a \"net negative\" for the economy. that sounds like you've already decided. if we're talking about national security or making sure we don't rely on other countries for essential goods, wouldn't protectionism be the \"correct\" choice there? isn't it more about long-term stability than just price tags?",
