      "content": "i hear you on the innovation thing, but that's just theory. in the real world, if we don't use tariffs right now, those domestic industries are just gonna go extinct before they can ever \"innovate.\" so isn't it basically a fact that tariffs are the only practical tool we have to prevent that, even if the economics aren't perfect?",
